                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d174">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13346: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief, United States Asiatic Fleet</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Yarnell</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of Naval Operations</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="8" xml:id="d174fn8">Copy of telegram from the Commander,
                        United States Yangtze Patrol (Le Breton), to the commanding officer of the
                        U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Monocacy;</hi> transmitted to the Department by
                        the Navy Department.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-29T12:12:00+08:00"
                            >June 29 [<hi rend="italic">30?</hi>], 1938—12:12 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>0029. Chinese Foreign Office advises river officially blocked above Lienchiachen
                    from 29 June but off record states river navigable along north bank slow speed
                    another 48 hours. Plan <hi rend="italic">Monocacy</hi> remain Kiukiang
                    unchanged.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
